                  </hi>. I am a chemist and druggist, and live at No. 147, oxford-street. I know Mr. Bray's omnibuses—I have observed them for about two or three months—I have observed two other omnibuses, with the name of "J. Bolton" on them—Chapel-place is a place where they generally stop, and if Bray's omnibus has stopped there to take passengers, or any passenger attempted to get in, the others drove in such a manner as to prevent their getting in—I have observed that fre<lb></lb>quently with those omnibuses—I cannot speak as to others—I have seen Mr. Bolton's more particularly.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Have you ever seen Bray's omnibuses interfering with those other omnibuses, and preventing people getting into them? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
