                  </hi>. I am a surgeon, and live at No. 14, High Holborn. I remember going by Mr. Bray'somnibus on the 18th of August—It took me up, and putu me down in Oxford-street—and on my return by it the "Emperor, Edmund Sylvester, 352, "would not allow me to get down at my own door—I suspect it was because they saw Mr. Bray take me from</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183509210216"></xptr>
               <p>my own door—they stopped to see me taken up, and I was stopped by the "Emperor" pulling up against my door, which would not allow me to get down at my own door, and I was obliged to get down in Kingsgate-street—I have seen opposition to Mr. Bray's omnibus at other times, one before and one behind it, so that I have been obliged to take another omnibus.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Have you ever seen Bray's omnibus acting in this way to the others, and annoying them? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Not in the least.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
